The Presidency has announced that another interview with President Muhammadu Buhari will be broadcast on government-owned Nigerian Television Authority (NTA) Friday night. Special Adviser to the President on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina, disclosed this in a statement on Friday, titled, ‘President Muhammadu Buhari In Exclusive Interview With NTA’.  According to him, the exclusive interview will be "revealing and educating". The statement said, “President Muhammadu Buhari grants Nigerian Television Authority an exclusive interview, from 8.30 pm, Friday, June 11, 2021. "It promises to be revealing and educating. Kindly keep a date." Buhari on Thursday featured on a morning programme on Arise TV where he answered some questions. However, he has been criticised for some of his positions as expressed during the interview.